results.name: Denominator: factorizations divided by strict factorizations A001055(n)/A045778(n).
comment: A factorization of n is a finite, nondecreasing sequence of positive integers > 1 with product n. It is strict if the factors are all different. Factorizations and strict factorizations are counted by A001055 and A045778 respectively.
xref: Positions of 1's include all elements of A001248 as well as A005117. The first position of a 1 that is not in A167207 is 128.
The same for integer partitions is A330995.
